13/08/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Investigators found a new mass grave where victims of the 1995 Srebrenica massacre may have been buried in the eastern village of Kamenica, near Zvornik, on Tuesday (August 12th). "The ditch is 10m long and 3m wide. Underneath the first layer of earth, we found the remains of about ten bodies," Murat Hurtic of the Bosnian Muslim commission for missing persons told AFP. Excavations will continue for about two weeks. Experts believe dozens of people were buried there. (AFP, France 24 - 12/08/08)
